CatDescriptText: These men belong to the VFW Post, possibly the William H. Carney Post in the Hill District. "Comradeship Industry" was their purpose as their motto was, "Keep them smiling in beds of white."
TitMainTitle: Two men in shirts, hats and sashes decorated with insects; hats read "Pennsylvania," one man's shirt with badge reading: Military Order of the Cootie / Comradeship Industry
